This repository is stdlib-only at runtime and carries no third-party runtime
dependencies (see `SBOM.md`). This NOTICE file is the project's **provenance
ledger**: the authoritative, per-piece attribution record for content that was
ported or adapted into this repository from an external source.

Why a ledger (and not just per-file frontmatter)
-------------------------------------------------
A `SKILL.md` frontmatter block can state a skill's origin, but frontmatter is
edited alongside the skill and travels with a single file. This NOTICE is the
single, catalog-wide, human-auditable record: one row per ported piece, naming
the exact upstream source, the pinned upstream commit, the upstream license,
and how the piece entered our tree (clean-room rewrite vs. verbatim port). The
mechanical import gate (`.claude/scripts/check-imported-skill.py`, PLAN-153
Wave D) reads this file directly: a ported skill cannot enter the catalog
unless a well-formed provenance row for its catalog path exists here. This
ledger is therefore load-bearing, not decorative.

How to read a row
-----------------
    <repo-relative target path> — <relationship> (<provenance>); imported from
    `<upstream>@<sha>` `<upstream subpath>`, ported under the <license>.

Rows are grouped by the batch that introduced them.

